Dependencies:

Description				  Library  Version
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
C++ template class array library          blitz++  (>= 0.9, 0.10 recommended)
Hierarchical data format 5                hdf5     (>= 1.8.4)
Fastest Fourier Transform of the West     fftw     (>= 3.2.2)
GNU scientific library                    gsl      (>= 1.13)
Open Computer Vision library              OpenCV   (>= 2.0)
QT4                                       Qt4      (>= 4.6.2)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

When the above-mentioned dependencies are met you should be able to build
the iRoCS Toolbox as follows:

./configure
make
make install

This will install the software to /usr/local. Especially if you do not have
super-user rights on the host system you can change the installation folder
using the "--prefix" option in configure. E.g. "./configure --prefix=~/iRoCS"
will install the iRoCS Toolbox into a subfolder called iRoCS in your home
folder.

All headers will be installed into the subfolder $(prefix)/include/irocs-toolbox.
